  <h1 class="article__title">Nothing is made alone</h1>

  <p>
    This site was designed, directed, and obsessed over by me — but it wouldn't exist
    without the tools, sounds, and open-source work of others. Here's who made it possible.
  </p>

  <h2>The slaps</h2>
  <p>
    Yes, the stickers actually make a sound. The slapping effect comes from
    <a href="https://pixabay.com/users/freesound_community-46691455/">freesound_community</a>
    on <a href="https://pixabay.com/">Pixabay</a>. Try clicking the portrait a few too many times.
  </p>

  <h2>The stack</h2>
  <p>
    Built with <a href="https://claude.ai/claude-code">Claude Code</a> as my co-pilot,
    <a href="https://www.11ty.dev/">Eleventy</a> as the static site generator, and
    <a href="https://pages.github.com/">GitHub Pages</a> for hosting. No frameworks,
    no bundlers, no build tools beyond what 11ty gives you out of the box.
    Vanilla HTML, CSS, and JS — the way the web was meant to taste.
  </p>

  <h2>The human</h2>
  <p>
    Design, direction, copy, and the questionable decision to add screen shake:
    Inti Valderas Caro.
  </p>

